ABUJA – The National Leader of the Ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has said that he discussed his presidential ambition with President Muhammadu Buhari, during which he told the President that he wants to “step into his shoes and not step on his toes.” Tinubu who’s currently meeting with the APC Caucus of the House of Representatives in Abuja said he remains the most competent of all other aspirants to govern the country come 2023. Details shortly.